OL,3,CJustice minister rules out appeal of
OL,4,Csex offender anonymity law
OL,6,FJustice Minister Naomi Long has said
OL,7,Fshe will not appeal a High Court
OL,8,Fjudgment over contentious sexual
OL,9,Foffender anonymity legislation.
OL,11,FMs Long said she had considered the
OL,12,Fviews of her ministerial colleagues
OL,13,Fwho "do not share" her concerns over
OL,14,Fthe "wider implications to the
OL,15,FAssembly" of the ruling.
OL,17,FThe Sexual Offences and Trafficking
OL,18,FVictims Act came into force in
OL,19,FNorthern Ireland last year.
